  "prompt": "What are the major events that happened in 1997?",
  "response": "1997 was a significant year with several major global events across various fields. Here are some of the key events from that year:\n\n1. **Princess Diana's Death**: On August 31, 1997, Princess Diana died in a car crash in the Pont de l'Alma tunnel in Paris, France. Her death was a significant global event and prompted an unprecedented outpouring of grief worldwide.\n\n2. **Hong Kong Handover**: On July 1, 1997, Hong Kong was handed over from the United Kingdom to the People's Republic of China, ending over 150 years of British colonial rule. This event marked the establishment of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region under the principle of \"one country, two systems.\"\n\n3. **Heaven's Gate Suicide**: In March 1997, 39 members of the Heaven's Gate cult were found dead in a mass suicide in Rancho Santa Fe, California. They believed that their souls would ascend to a spacecraft following the Hale-Bopp Comet.\n\n4. **Pathfinder Lands on Mars**: NASA's Pathfinder spacecraft successfully landed on Mars on July 4, 1997. The mission provided new insights into the Martian environment and included the first successful deployment of a rover on the Martian surface, named Sojourner.\n\n5. **Mongolia Elects Democratic President**: In May 1997, Mongolia elected Natsagiin Bagabandi as president in a peaceful transition of power, marking a significant step in the country's post-communist political development.\n\n6. **Kyoto Protocol**: The Kyoto Protocol was adopted on December 11, 1997, in Kyoto, Japan. This international treaty aimed to reduce greenhouse gas emissions and combat climate change by setting binding obligations for industrialized countries.\n\n7. **Stock Market Mini-Crash**: On October 27, 1997, global stock markets experienced a significant decline, most notably the Dow Jones Industrial Average, which fell by 554 points in one day, leading to a brief market panic.\n\n8. **Introduction of DVDs**: 1997 saw the widespread introduction of DVDs (Digital Versatile Discs), which quickly became a popular format for movie and video distribution, eventually replacing VHS tapes.\n\n9. **Titanic Release**: James Cameron's epic film \"Titanic\" premiered on December 19, 1997. It became a cultural phenomenon, eventually winning 11 Academy Awards and becoming one of the highest-grossing films of all time.\n\nThese events represent just a few highlights from 1997, a year of notable political, cultural, and technological milestones.",
